Demo App Usage Guide
This app provides users with a centralized platform to manage and edit data related to aircraft operations, including aircrafts, pilots, companies, passengers, and locations. All of this functionality is accessible through the Resources page, which consolidates the management of these resources.

Navigation
The app has a navigation bar at the top that includes the following pages:

Home: The landing page with an input field for querying the AI and a display area for responses.
Resources: The main page for managing all resource data related to aircraft operations.
Dangerous Goods: A section for managing information about hazardous materials.
Reference Charts: Quick reference charts for important operational data.
Variables: A page to view and adjust key operational settings.
Home Page
Prompt Input: Enter any question or request for help into the input box labeled "Need help with something?"
Submit Query: Click the "+" button to submit your query to the AI. The response will be displayed below the input box.
Resources Page
The Resources page is your central hub for managing all key data. From this page, you can view, add, edit, and delete records for aircrafts, pilots, companies, passengers, and locations. Below is a detailed breakdown of what fields can be edited for each type of resource:

Aircrafts
Editable Fields:

Registration Number: The aircraft's unique identifier.
Model: The model of the aircraft.
Maximum Takeoff Weight (MTOW): The maximum allowable weight for the aircraft, including fuel, passengers, and cargo.
Empty Weight: The weight of the aircraft without any passengers, cargo, or fuel.
Fuel Capacity: The amount of fuel the aircraft can carry.
How to Edit: To change any of these details, navigate to the Resources page, locate the aircraft record, click on it to open the edit form, make your changes, and save the record.

Pilots
Editable Fields:

First Name
Last Name
License Number: The pilot's certification number.
Ratings: Specific ratings or qualifications the pilot holds.
Medical Certificate Expiry: The expiration date of the pilot's medical certification.
How to Edit: To update pilot information, go to the Resources page, find the relevant pilot record, click to edit, update the fields as needed, and save the changes.

Companies
Editable Fields:

Company Name
Address
Contact Information: Phone number and email for the company.
Industry Type
How to Edit: Company records can be updated via the Resources page by selecting the company entry, editing the necessary fields, and saving the updated information.

Passengers
Editable Fields:

First Name
Last Name
Email
Weight: The weight of the passenger, which may be used for load balancing.
Luggage: Description of the luggage the passenger is carrying.
How to Edit: Passenger information can be edited by accessing the Resources page, selecting the passenger record, making changes to the required fields, and saving the record.

Locations
Editable Fields:

Location Name
Coordinates: Latitude and longitude of the location.
Description: A brief description of the location.
How to Edit: Location details can be modified on the Resources page by selecting the location entry, making the desired updates, and saving the record.

Dangerous Goods
The Dangerous Goods section allows you to manage records specific to hazardous materials that may be transported. You can view, add, edit, or delete records related to dangerous goods.

Editable Fields:
Material Name
Hazard Class
UN Number: The United Nations number assigned to the hazardous material.
Description: Additional details about the material.
Reference Charts
The Reference Charts section provides quick access to operational charts. These charts are read-only and are used for reference purposes only.

Variables
The Variables page is where you can view and adjust key operational settings or variables. However, it is important to note that aircraft weight is not adjusted here. Instead, use the Resources page to update the aircraft weight or other specific fields for different resource types.

Knowing all this, respond to the following.

"{{this.params.prompt}}"

SELECT 
  raglan.manifests.id AS id,
  raglan.manifests.date AS date,
  source_location.location_name AS source,
  destination_location.location_name AS destination,
  raglan.manifests.departure_time AS departure_time,
  raglan.aircrafts.registration AS aircraft,
  raglan.aircrafts.ac_weight AS aircraft_weight,
  raglan.pilots.name AS pilot,
  raglan.pilots.weight AS pilot_weight,
  raglan.manifests.fuel_percentage AS fuel_percentage,

  -- Fuel Weight Calculation (handling NULL with COALESCE)
  COALESCE(raglan.manifests.fuel_percentage::numeric, 0) * 941 AS fuel_weight,

  -- Passenger JSON Aggregation
  JSON_AGG(
    JSON_BUILD_OBJECT(
      'name', CONCAT(raglan.passengers.first_name, ' ', raglan.passengers.last_name),
      'pax_weight', raglan.passengers.weight_lb,
      'cargo_pcs', raglan.manifest_passengers.cargo_pcs,
      'cargo_weight', raglan.manifest_passengers.cargo_weight
    )
  ) FILTER (WHERE raglan.manifest_passengers.id IS NOT NULL) AS passengers,

  -- Cargo JSON Aggregation
  JSON_AGG(
    JSON_BUILD_OBJECT(
      'name', raglan.manifest_cargo.name,
      'pcs', raglan.manifest_cargo.pcs,
      'weight', raglan.manifest_cargo.weight
    )
  ) FILTER (WHERE raglan.manifest_cargo.id IS NOT NULL) AS cargo,

  -- Calculated Totals
  COALESCE(SUM(raglan.passengers.weight_lb), 0) AS total_pax_weight,
  COALESCE(SUM(raglan.manifest_passengers.cargo_pcs) + SUM(raglan.manifest_cargo.pcs), 0) AS total_cargo_pcs,
  COALESCE(SUM(raglan.manifest_passengers.cargo_weight) + SUM(raglan.manifest_cargo.weight), 0) AS total_cargo_weight,
  COALESCE(SUM(raglan.passengers.weight_lb) + SUM(raglan.manifest_passengers.cargo_weight) + SUM(raglan.manifest_cargo.weight), 0) AS total_internal_weight,
  
  -- Total aircraft, pilot, and fuel weight
  (raglan.aircrafts.ac_weight + raglan.pilots.weight + COALESCE(raglan.manifests.fuel_percentage::numeric, 0) * 941) AS total_ac_pilot_fuel_weight,

  -- Total cargo and passengers
  COALESCE(SUM(raglan.passengers.weight_lb + raglan.manifest_passengers.cargo_weight + raglan.manifest_cargo.weight), 0) AS total_cargo_pax,

  -- Final weight calculation
  (
    (raglan.aircrafts.ac_weight + raglan.pilots.weight + COALESCE(raglan.manifests.fuel_percentage::numeric, 0) * 941) + 
    COALESCE(SUM(raglan.passengers.weight_lb + raglan.manifest_passengers.cargo_weight + raglan.manifest_cargo.weight), 0)
  ) AS total_augw

FROM raglan.manifests

-- Joins
LEFT JOIN raglan.locations AS source_location ON raglan.manifests.source_id = source_location.id
LEFT JOIN raglan.locations AS destination_location ON raglan.manifests.destination_id = destination_location.id
LEFT JOIN raglan.aircrafts ON raglan.manifests.aircraft_id = raglan.aircrafts.id
LEFT JOIN raglan.pilots ON raglan.manifests.pilot_id = raglan.pilots.id
LEFT JOIN raglan.manifest_passengers ON raglan.manifests.id = raglan.manifest_passengers.manifest_id
LEFT JOIN raglan.passengers ON raglan.manifest_passengers.passenger_id = raglan.passengers.id
LEFT JOIN raglan.manifest_cargo ON raglan.manifests.id = raglan.manifest_cargo.manifest_id

WHERE raglan.manifests.id = '{{this.params.manifest_id}}'

GROUP BY 
  raglan.manifests.id, 
  source_location.location_name, 
  destination_location.location_name, 
  raglan.manifests.date, 
  raglan.manifests.departure_time, 
  raglan.aircrafts.registration, 
  raglan.aircrafts.ac_weight, 
  raglan.pilots.name, 
  raglan.pilots.weight, 
  raglan.manifests.fuel_percentage;
